# PocketForge initrd M1.B-mode marker.
#
# Presence of this file as /etc/pocketforge-m1b-mode INSIDE the initrd cpio
# switches /init's final handoff from `switch_root` to an interactive busybox
# shell on the serial console, AFTER the PowerVR modules load successfully.
#
# This satisfies M1.B's G0 "first SD that boots to a shell" without needing a
# separate Debian rootfs build: the empty 64 MiB userdata partition is never
# mounted; the shell runs inside the initramfs.
#
# The build stages this file into the cpio ONLY when assembling an M1.B-mode
# initrd (build.sh --m1b-mode). M1.C onward omits it, so the SAME /init source
# takes the normal switch_root path. (bd tsp-iuz.1.11, tsp-iuz.1.6)
#
# The file's CONTENT is irrelevant — only its presence matters. This text is
# documentation for anyone who extracts the cpio.
